<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-4841] NetworkClient should only consider a connection to be fail after attempt to connect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4841</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4820&quot; title=&quot;ConsumerNetworkClient.send() should not require global lock&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-4820&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-4820&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; allows new request to be enqueued to unsent by user thread while some other thread does poll(...). This causes problem in the following scenario:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thread A calls poll(...) and is blocked on select(...)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thread B enqueues a request into unsent of ConsumerNetworkClient for node N&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thread A calls checkDisconnects(now) -&amp;gt; client.connectionFailed(N)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Because no attempts have been made to connection to node N yet, there is no state for node N and connectionFailed(N) would throw exception. Note that this problem only occurs when one thread is able to enqueue requests while another thread is in the process of `poll(...)`&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The solution is to only consider a connection has failed if attempts have been made to connect to this node AND the connection state is DISCONNECTED.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
